# Ensure Domain Model Usage on Code

## Domain Specification Location

The domain specification MUST reside in [`docs/domain-specification.md`](../../docs/domain-specification.md).  
It MUST contain **"Ubiquitous Language"**. Also follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Pre-Change Checklist (Before Any Code Change)

1. **Read** the domain specification (especially Ubiquitous Language).
2. **Question the change against the domain** — new entities, roles, auth rules, UI labels?
3. Update the specification **first** if the domain changes.

**Do NOT write code or tests until answered.**

## Coding Rules

Identifiers MUST use domain terms: **User**, **Profile**, **Role**, **Login**, **Assign profiles** — not `UserData`, `doLogin`, `setFlag`.

See [passport-tell-dont-ask.mdc](passport-tell-dont-ask.mdc), [passport-law-of-demeter.mdc](passport-law-of-demeter.mdc).

## Testing Rules

Tests use domain language (`Given.admin()`, `shouldRejectLoginForDisabledUser`).

## Post-Change Update Rule

Update `docs/domain-specification.md` and [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) when concepts, routes, or invariants change.

## Violation Handling

Refactor technical names to domain terms when touching violating code.
